<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code calls strlen(ldrv->drv_name) without first validating that ldrv->drv_name is non-NULL and points to a NUL-terminated buffer. If drv_name is NULL or points to a character array that is not NUL-terminated, strlen will read beyond the bounds of the referenced object, violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
